    purport: `
        <p><strong>1. Universality of the Vision:</strong> This is not limited to a single class of beings; all levels of existence—divine, semi-divine, and subtle—are witnessing the same reality. This emphasizes that the universal form transcends all categories and is relevant to every dimension of existence.</p>

        <p><strong>2. Collective Astonishment:</strong> The shared reaction of amazement indicates that even the most knowledgeable beings are confronted with something beyond their comprehension. This suggests that no level of knowledge fully contains the infinite.</p>

        <p><strong>3. Collapse of Superiority:</strong> Even higher beings, often considered powerful or wise, stand equally astonished. This removes hierarchical pride and places all observers on the same level before the infinite.</p>

        <p><strong>Conclusion:</strong> This verse reinforces the idea that ultimate reality surpasses all forms of understanding. No matter the level of knowledge or power, the infinite remains beyond complete grasp. This realization humbles all beings and highlights the vastness that unites them in shared awe.</p>
    `
